            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "My current idea would be to extend `nvim_try_resize` and all functions associated to also accept `pixel_width` and `pixel_height`. As far as I understand, this is how `SIGWINCH` is handled in the TUI, which would be where we get `ws_xpixel` and `ws_ypixel` along with the rows and columns. Then handling `TIOCGWINSZ` would just mean passing these around along with the rows and columns and including them in `pty_proc_spawn` and `pty_proc_resize`.\n\nMaybe someone more knowledgeable can confirm, that I am not completely on the wrong track and that it is ok to change the `nvim_try_resize` api.",
