            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I mentioned it in a few other places, but implementation of this could be greatly helped with [chafa](https://github.com/hpjansson/chafa/). Chafa takes in a few image encodings, but multiplexes out to virtually all terminal graphics outputs as strings. This should enable the neovim devs to pick whichever ingress image api(s) they wish, then get an image encoded in such a way it will render on any terminal (though I'd reccomend checking for \"symbol\" mode and refusing to render that mode, at least by default)\n\nI'm a bit worried, however, about image placement, so perhaps that isn't a viable solution.",
