            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I'd be happy to restart work on #32408. That'd at least allow any programs that use unicode place holders to work.\n\nThere were some discussion points in that PR that I don't feel super confident in making a decision about, mainly what event should report pixel sizes from UIs and how to change the API with #31903 unresolved. From the comments in #32408, I agree that pixel window sizes should be tracked per UI, but am unconvinced by them being floats or tracked per window or any other complication that'd only serve some yet unknown usecase. I think just properly answering to `ioctl` in term buffers is enough of a scope.\n\nThat said, for programs that don't use unicode placeholders to be supported I think we need #39432.",
